  "text": "We improve the four-nodes-per-cycle FSD architecture described in [CITATION_1] We can see that both FSD and K-best SD exhibit performance gaps compared with the optimal SESD algorithm. The gaps can be compensated in certain degree by increasing nodes, but the K-best SD with K = 12 needs to visit (16+3×12×16) = 592 nodes, which is much higher compared with the FSD. Therefore we conclude that among sub-optimal algorithms, the FSD algorithm is more efficient than the K-best algorithm.",
